ls\ncost_per_pencil = 10\nnumber_of_pencils = 5\ntotal_cost_of_pencils = cost_per_pencil * number_of_pencils\nremaining_after_pencils = remaining_after_deposit - total_cost_of_pencils\n\n# Cost of pens\ncost_per_pen = 25\nnumber_of_pens = remaining_after_pencils // cost_per_pen\n\nprint(number_of_pens)\n```\n```output\n4\n```\nThe final answer is that John can buy \\(\\boxed{4}\\) pens.\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
