[32m'Masked text for sample 3, segment 6042-6743: `\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the given answer for the area of triangle \\( OAB \\) is correct, we can use the formula for the area of a triangle formed by two vectors \\(\\overrightarrow{OA}\\) and \\(\\overrightarrow{OB}\\) in three-dimensional space. The area \\( A \\) of the triangle is given by:\n\n\\[\nA = \\frac{1}{2} \\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\|\n\\]\n\nwhere \\(\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\) is the cross product of the vectors \\(\\overrightarrow{OA}\\) and \\(\\overrightarrow{OB}\\).\n\nGiven:\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix}, \\quad \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\\\ -2 \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix}\n\\]\n\nThe cross product \\(\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\) is calculated as:\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 1 & 2 & 3 \\\\ -3 & -2 & 1 \\end{vmatrix}\n\\]\n\nThis determinant expands to:\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\mathbf{i}(2 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-2)) - \\mathbf{j}(1 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-3)) + \\mathbf{k}(1 \\cdot (-2) - 2 \\cdot (-3))\n\\]\n\nSimplifying each component:\n\n- \\(\\mathbf{i}\\) component: \\(2 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-2) = 2 + 6 = 8\\)\n- \\(\\mathbf{j}\\) component: \\(1 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-3) = 1 + 9 = 10\\)\n- \\(\\mathbf{k}\\) component: \\(1 \\cdot (-2) - 2 \\cdot (-3) = -2 + 6 = 4\\)\n\nThus, the cross product is:\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\\\ -10 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix}\n\\]\n\nThe magnitude of this vector is:\n\n\\[\n\\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\| = \\sqrt{8^2 + (-10)^2 + 4^2} = \\sqrt{64 + 100 + 16} = \\sqrt{180}\n\\]\n\nThe area of the triangle is:\n\n\\[\nA = \\frac{1}{2} \\sqrt{180} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times \\sqrt{36 \\times 5} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 6\\sqrt{5} = 3\\sqrt{5}\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the given answer \\(3\\sqrt{5}\\) is correct.<|im_end|>\n'[0m
