[32m'Masked text for sample 3, segment 5416-6052: .\n\nLet me try again.\n\nThe given vectors are $\\overrightarrow{OA} = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix}$ and $\\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\\\ -2 \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix}.$ The area of the triangle formed by vectors $\\overrightarrow{OA}$ and $\\overrightarrow{OB}$ can be found using the cross product of these vectors. The area of the triangle is given by half the magnitude of the cross product of the vectors.\n\nThe cross product $\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}$ is calculated as follows:\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 1 & 2 & 3 \\\\ -3 & -2 & 1 \\end{vmatrix} = \\mathbf{i}(2 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-2)) - \\mathbf{j}(1 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-3)) + \\mathbf{k}(1 \\cdot (-2) - 2 \\cdot (-3))\n\\]\n\\[\n= \\mathbf{i}(2 + 6) - \\mathbf{j}(1 + 9) + \\mathbf{k}(-2 + 6) = 8\\mathbf{i} - 10\\mathbf{j} + 4\\mathbf{k} = \\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\\\ -10 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix}\n\\]\n\nThe magnitude of this cross product is:\n\\[\n\\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\| = \\sqrt{8^2 + (-10)^2 + 4^2} = \\sqrt{64 + 100 + 16} = \\sqrt{180} = 6\\sqrt{5}\n\\]\n\nThe area of the triangle is half of this magnitude:\n\\[\n\\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{2} \\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\| = \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot 6\\sqrt{5} = 3\\sqrt{5}\n\\]\n\nThus, the area of triangle $OAB$ is $\\boxed{3\\sqrt{5}}$.\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Define the vectors OA and OB\nOA = np.array([1, 2, 3])\nOB = np.array([-3, -2, 1])\n\n# Calculate the cross product of OA and OB\ncross_product = np.cross(OA, OB)\n\n# Calculate the magnitude of the cross product\nmagnitude = np.linalg.norm(cross_product)\n\n# The area of the triangle is half the magnitude of the cross product\narea = 0.5 * magnitude\nprint(area)\n```\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n'[0m
