s dug by the dog while Nate is on vacation is:\n   \\[\n   6 \\text{ holes/day} \\times 14 \\text{ days} = 84 \\text{ holes}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Daily Net Change in Holes**: When Nate returns, he fills in 9 holes per day, but the dog continues to dig 6 holes each night. Therefore, the net change in the number of holes per day is:\n   \\[\n   9 \\text{ holes filled} - 6 \\text{ holes dug} = 3 \\text{ holes filled per day}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Time to Fill All Holes**: To fill all 84 holes, Nate needs to fill 3 holes per day. The number of days required to fill all the holes is:\n   \\[\n   \\frac{84 \\text{ holes}}{3 \\text{ holes/day}} = 28 \\text{ days}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Convert Days to Weeks**: Since there are 7 days in a week, the number of weeks it takes Nate to fill all the holes is:\n   \\[\n   \\frac{28 \\text{ days}}{7 \\text{ days/week}} = 4 \\text{ weeks}\n   \\]\n\nBased on this analysis, the answer provided (4 weeks) is correct.<|im_end|>\n"[0m
